00:52:04.590 --> 00:52:06.660
do you have a
traditional hierarchy?

00:52:06.660 --> 00:52:08.340
Or do you have a whole-ocracy?

00:52:08.340 --> 00:52:12.000
Is there someone whose job it is
to make a call about what's in,

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:12.530
what's out?

00:52:12.530 --> 00:52:15.960
Like, that's well-defined
and established?

00:52:15.960 --> 00:52:18.210
BERNARD PETIOT: Somewhat,
although it has a little bit

00:52:18.210 --> 00:52:19.860
of a holistic approach.

00:52:19.860 --> 00:52:24.120
When it was [NON-ENGLISH]
as the sole owner,

00:52:24.120 --> 00:52:29.430
I would have to say to being
present that he would say, OK,

00:52:29.430 --> 00:52:31.570
I will give you
another three weeks.

00:52:31.570 --> 00:52:36.790
And if you don't convince me,
then that's the end of it.

00:52:36.790 --> 00:52:38.812
Now that has changed
a little bit.

00:52:38.812 --> 00:52:40.270
[NON-ENGLISH] is
not there anymore.

00:52:40.270 --> 00:52:45.540
So the director of creation is
exercising that responsibility.

00:52:45.540 --> 00:52:48.990
And then eventually
the executive producer

00:52:48.990 --> 00:52:51.368
may at some point
also exercise that.

00:52:51.368 --> 00:52:52.410
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Got it.

